Pro Q4

Highest possible sound quality, unrivalled interface workflow

Unrivalled sound and workflow

An equalizer is probably the tool you use most while mixing and mastering, so you need the best of the best. FabFilter Pro-Q 4 delivers with the highest possible sound quality, a very extensive feature set, and a gorgeous, innovative interface with unrivalled ease of use.

Buy now 30-day trial

FabFilter Pro-Q has one of the best GUIs of any EQ out there and sonically compares to the best.

FabFilter Pro-Q has one of the best GUIs of any EQ out there and sonically compares to the best.

Dave Pensado (Grammy Award-winning mix engineer)

Mixing and mastering features

Pro-Q 4 offers everything that a demanding engineer could wish for: top-quality linear phase operation in addition to the zero latency and unique Natural Phase modes, smooth dynamic and spectral EQ, per-band mid/side processing, full surround support (up to Dolby Atmos 9.1.6), an intelligent solo feature, optional Auto Gain and a built-in, fully customizable spectrum analyzer.

Effortlessly sculpt your sound

FabFilter Pro-Q 4 is designed to help you achieve your sound in the quickest way possible. Via the large interactive EQ display, you can add or sketch bands where you need them, enable dynamic EQ for any band, and select and edit multiple bands at once.

Unique features like Spectrum Grab, Full Screen mode and EQ Match will speed up your workflow even more. Try it yourself!

FabFilter goodies

Of course, you also get all the usual FabFilter goodies: perfectly tuned knobs, interactive MIDI Learn, undo/redo and A/B switch, Smart Parameter Interpolation for smooth parameter transitions, an extensive help file with interactive help hints, sample-accurate automation, advanced optimization and much more.

Instance List

All your Pro-Q 4 instances in one interface

With Pro-Q 4, you can control any other plug-in instance in your session from a single interface, easily navigating the list by filtering, pinning and zooming as desired.

You will discover that the Instance List is a huge time-saver, making it much easier to setup initial EQing when starting your mix session.

Spectral dynamics processing

Precise treatment of problem frequencies

In Spectral dynamics mode, Pro-Q 4 doesn't change the gain of the whole band, but triggers per specific frequency within a band when it exceeds the threshold, leaving other frequencies untouched. This is a great way of treating varying problem frequencies.

Typically, you would need a separate and often complex plug-in for this type of processing, but Pro-Q 4 makes the process simple to use and easy to understand, as a natural extension of normal dynamic processing.

EQ Sketch and usability

Just draw the curve you need

Setting up initial EQ settings in an equalizer often involves adding a few general bands to get started, like a low cut filter, a few bell filters and a high shelf, creating a general starting point.

Wouldn't it be great if you could draw that curve in one gesture? Well... now you can with EQ Sketch!

Key features

  1. improved Highest possible sound quality
  2. Up to 24 EQ bands
  3. improved Optional Dynamic EQ mode for all bands (Bell and Shelf shapes), with adjustable attack and release, optional side-chain filtering and external triggering
  4. new Advanced Spectral dynamics processing, to effectively and precisely treat problem frequencies in your audio
  5. Full immersive / Dolby Atmos functionality (up to 9.1.6), with intelligent speaker selection
  6. new EQ Sketch: just draw the desired EQ curve in one go to setup initial EQing
  7. improved Continuous slope setting up to 96 dB/oct for all filter types and ultra-steep 'Brickwall' slope setting for LP and HP filters
  8. new Work fast and efficiently: use the Instance list to view and control any other Pro-Q 4 instance in your session
  9. improved Gorgeous Retina interface with large interactive EQ display, multi-band selection and editing for maximum ease of use and efficiency
  10. Per-band mid/side or left/right processing, so you can EQ the mid, side, left or right signals separately
  11. improved Operates in zero latency mode, high quality linear phase mode with adjustable latency or the unique Natural Phase mode
  12. new Use the Gentle and Warm Character modes to add analog warmth to your mixes
  13. Spectrum Grab: just grab and adjust a peak in the real-time spectrum analyzer right away!
  14. Resizable interface, full screen mode and customizable scaling
  1. improved Filter shapes: Bell, Notch, High/Low Shelf, High/Low Cut, Band Pass, Tilt Shelf, Flat Tilt and All Pass
  2. improved EQ Match feature to automatically match the spectrum of another Pro-Q 4 instance or an external signal
  3. improved Built-in spectrum analyzer with Pre-EQ, Post-EQ and external spectrum visualization, adjustable range, speed, resolution, tilt, freeze and collision detection
  4. Auto Gain and Gain Scale
  5. Optional piano roll display to quantize EQ frequencies to musical notes
  6. Flat Tilt filter shape, a flat tilting correction curve over the whole audible frequency spectrum
  7. Different display ranges: 3 dB and 6 dB ranges for mastering, 12 dB and 30 dB for mixing
  8. Intelligent solo mode makes it easy to find problem frequencies and hear the effect of a band
  9. Phase Invert option to change polarity
  10. Extreme CPU optimization: Pro-Q 4 uses very little CPU and memory, so you can use hundreds of instances in a session
  11. new Copy and paste EQ bands or presets between plug-in instances
  12. Supports common Pro Tools hardware control surfaces
  13. Double-click text entry of parameter values
  14. MIDI Learn with option to control the currently active band
  15. GPU-powered graphics acceleration
  16. Large output level meter with peak level readout
  17. Undo/redo and A/B comparison
  18. Smart Parameter Interpolation
  19. Sample-accurate automation of all parameters
  20. Extensive help file with interactive help hints
  21. Available in VST, VST3, Audio Units, CLAP, AAX Native and AudioSuite formats
